<div class="policy-container">
  <h1 class="policy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>

  

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
    Swarga Dhamam is committed to protecting the privacy, dignity, and personal information of families who avail our services. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard information.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>
     We may collect limited information such as:

Name of the deceased

Name and contact details of family members

Date and time of services

Ritual or service-related details shared voluntarily

📌 We collect only what is necessary to provide proper last-rite services.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>How We Use the Information</h3>
    <p>
      The information collected is used only to:

Arrange cremation and religious services

Maintain internal service records

Communicate with family members regarding timings or arrangements

We do not use information for marketing or commercial purposes.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Information Sharing</h3>
    <p>
  We do not sell, rent, or share personal information with third parties

Information is shared only when required by law or with consent of the family

Priests or service helpers receive only essential details needed for rituals
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Data Protection & Security</h3>
    <p>
     All records are handled with strict confidentiality

Physical and digital records are protected against unauthorized access

Only authorized staff or management can access service-related information
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Respect for Dignity & Religious Sensitivity</h3>
    <p>
      We deeply respect:

The privacy of grieving families

The religious and cultural sentiments of Hindu traditions

No photos, videos, or personal details are shared publicly without explicit permission.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Website Data (if applicable)</h3>
    <p>
     If our website uses:

Contact forms

Appointment or enquiry forms

The submitted information is used only to respond to the request and is not stored longer than necessary.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Cookies</h3>
    <p>
    Our website may use basic cookies only to:

Improve website performance

Enhance user experience

No personal tracking or advertising cookies are used.

    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Children’s Privacy</h3>
    <p>
     Swarga Dhamam does not knowingly collect personal information from children.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <h3>Changes to Privacy Policy</h3>
